# Character Rendering

`CharacterRenderer` is intentionally sprite-agnostic. Keep its public API stable:

- `init(host)`, `setView(partial)`, `resize()`, `destroy()`.
- The engine/layer feeds state via `setView`; it must not know whether the
  character is drawn with Graphics or sprite sheets.

When upgrading the placeholder to real sprite sheets, reimplement the private
draw/animate methods only. Do NOT change the public API or the engine wiring.

## Visemes and lighting

- Mouth/viseme geometry lives in `visemes.ts` (`MOUTH_SHAPES`). Add new shapes
  there, not inline in the renderer.
- Honor lighting `character: on | off`:
  - `on` = normal palette.
  - `off` = flat silhouette in the theme background colour (no face/mouth).
- Body animation (`walkIn`, `idle`, `gesture`, `wave`) is driven by transforms in
  the ticker; redraw geometry only when palette/emotion/mouth actually change.
